            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001509_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><opener><dateline rend="right"><placeName>Shupanga</placeName> <date when="1859-11-05">5 <choice><abbr>Nov</abbr><expan>November</expan></choice> 1859</date></dateline>  
<lb/><salute>My Dear <choice><sic>Dr</sic><corr>Dr.</corr></choice> <persName>Kirk</persName></salute><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><hi rend="red">18</hi></opener>
<lb/><p>You will no
<lb/>doubt be disappointed
<lb/>at not finding us
<lb/>here - but there is
<lb/>no help for it as
<lb/>we are sinking.
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>We waited at
<lb/><unclear cert="high"><settlement>Shambara</settlement></unclear> till
<lb/>yesterday morning
<lb/>(5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> I - We had
<lb/>made a good deal</p>
<lb/><cb rend="vertical"></cb><ab>I saw hardship for paper you see</ab><!-- text is vertical, doesn't seem to continue specifically from anywhere, including page 4. Not sure how to code, had troubles getting greenlit, formatted best I could. BL-->

	<pb facs="liv_001509_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><p>of water and had
<lb/>to pump during the
<lb/>night while <persName>Rowe</persName>
<lb/>was away - but - 
<lb/>lying in a still
<lb/>place the leak seemed
<lb/>to fill up. As you
<lb/>did not make
<lb/>your appearance
<lb/>I resolved to run
<lb/>down here for
<lb/>food for the crew - 
<lb/>and went to bed
<lb/>last night all night



	<pb facs="liv_001509_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>in the morning
<lb/>we found the <unclear cert="medium">right</unclear>
<lb/>hand after <unclear cert="low">hold but</unclear>
<lb/>forehold as well
<lb/>as stoke hole with
<lb/>a large quantity of
<lb/>water - this is
<lb/>in addition the the
<lb/>constant leak where
<lb/>the men sleep - Tried
<lb/>to stop the leak <unclear>as</unclear>
<lb/>after hold &amp; failed
<lb/>We have to pump
<lb/>every little while


	<pb facs="liv_001509_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>the only chance of
<lb/>saving her is to get
<lb/>her <unclear>beaden northern</unclear>
<lb/>loss of time. We are
<lb/>Therefore cutting wood
<lb/>today &amp; will trim down
<lb/>tomorrow to <placeName>Kogone</placeName>
<lb/>I have a whaler<!--pretty sure I read it right, but I don't know why he says "whaler" here. BL--> for
<lb/>you. You must just
<lb/>do the best you
<lb/>can in this case - I
<lb/>leave your letters - Our
<lb/><unclear>town</unclear> you will see how
<lb/>We have a small square
<lb/>box of this for you heard
<lb/>My daughter is better
<lb/></p><closer rend="right"><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer>



            </div>
